Precondition: Sublime Text3 & Anaconda3

1. Ctrl + shift + p
    search：Package Control : Install Package --> enter
    input: conda --> enter

2. Tools -> Build System -> Conda
    Preferences -> package settings -> conda -> setting user
    copy the following settings：
      //Executable is anaconda default python path
      //environment_directory is anaconda environment
     
      // Default settings for sublime-text-conda:
      {
      // executable is the path to anaconda's python
      // this python executable is used in order to find conda
      //"executable": "~/anaconda3/bin/python3",
      "executable": "d:/ProgramData/Anaconda3/python",

      // Directory in which the conda envs are stored
      // Default location is the user's home directory
      //"environment_directory": "~/anaconda3/envs/",
      "environment_directory": "d:/ProgramData/Anaconda3/envs/",

      // configuration is the path to conda's configuration file
      "configuration": "~/.condarc"
      }
3. using
   Ctrl + shift + p
   input conda
   presents conda command list
   setting or activate new environment
